     MTV Networks abandoned plan to use name TV Land for planned

     MTV Networks abandoned plan to use name TV Land for planned
new cable network after it lost another bid for right to use name,
spokeswoman said.  Company still hasn't selected new name, hopes to
do so soon, she said.  Seventh U.S. Appeals Court, Chicago, turned
down company's request to stay preliminary injunction against using
name, issued earlier by lower court.  Name is subject of trademark
infringement suit filed by Chicago-area electronic retailer also
called TV Land.  New network is to focus on classic broadcast TV
shows, be ad-supported, distributed free to cable operators.




