     *ATC's Walt Ciciora says the possibility of accelerating the
setting of an HDTV standard by merging two or more of the
proposed systems faces serious obstacles.  The reasons: highly
divergent systems, large egos of the companies involved, and the
likelihood that "the little guys would cry foul."



