AT&T WINS $32M NAVY CONTRACT

AT&T has signed a $32-million contract with the U.S. Navy's Space
and Naval Warfare Systems Command to provide technological
services for a T-AGS 45-class vessel to be built for the Military
Sealift Command at Avondale Industries' New Orleans, La.,
shipyard. AT&T will provide the survey ship with shipboard
electronics, shipboard machinery, and engineering services.




