CSC TO SUPPORT NASA PROGRAMS

Computer Sciences Corp. has been selected by the NASA for a
contract valued at $65.7 million for engineering support
services, the company announced.

Under the contract to be negotiated, the company will support
sounding rocket, balloon and aeronautical programs and launch
range projects at NASA's facility at Wallop Island, Va.  The
facility is a unit of Goddard Space Flight Center, Md.




