TECHNOLOGY ALERT via NewsNet
January/February 1996

JAPANESE USE OF TITANIUM ALLOYS AND TITANIUM ALUMINIDES
FOR AUTOMOTIVE APPLICATIONS

Summarizes information obtained (in Dec. 1993)
involving the use of titanium alloys and titanium
aluminides for automotive applications.  Most of the
information was obtained from a one-day visit to Toyota
Central Research and Development Laboratories with Dr.
Takoshi Saito, and discussions with Prof. Richard
Wagner of GKSS during the SAMPE 93 Conference.

