UNITED STATES: ENTITY CLASSIFICATION

The IRS and Treasury have advised tax practitioners that publication
date for the "check the box" regulatory proposal for classifying
entities will be delayed into 1996. A simplified system of classifying
international entities is apparently controversial within the IRS and
is holding up the project.

Regulation writers apparently view the proposal as unduly taxpayer
favourable and are opposed to granting taxpayers any leeway in
classifying foreign entities. The overall project may be severed into
domestic and international projects to break the log jam. It is also
reported that the status of one person entitles will not be addressed
in the regulatory proposal.



