NovAtel Communications Ltd., 1020 64th Ave. N.E., Calgary, Alberta T2E 7V8,

NovAtel Communications Ltd., 1020 64th Ave. N.E., Calgary, Alberta T2E 7V8,
403/295-4500, and Northern Telecom Inc., 2100 Lakeside Blvd., Richardson, TX
75081, 214/301-2000, have demonstrated the first commercial intersystem
handoff between 2 cellular carriers using switches built by different
manufacturers.  The handoffs have been demonstrated between the AGT Cellular
system, which uses a NovAtel 800 CM switch, serving the greater Calgary area of
Alberta and "et" Cellular, a division of Edmonton Telephones, which uses the
Northern Telecom DMS-MTX switch to serve Edmonton, Alberta.  The intersystem
handoff uses the Telecommunications Industries Association (TIA) TR45.2
committee's IS-41 protocol.



