works car-to-car with the cigarette lighter plug or can be converted into a
transportable by adding a battery.  "We're hoping that users will buy a
transceiver and a bag and use the handset from the car," Queen said.
Suggested retail:  $699.
    Technophone also introduced a new program for dealers and sales people,
Technopoints '90.  Every phone sold earns the salesperson or dealer a certain
number of points.  The points can then be traded for a variety of prizes out of
a glossy catalog.



